> Rain or shine, warm or cool, it's tough not to crave a big bowl of soup (i.e. the
> culinary equivalent of a bear hug). Tonight's soup is chock full of goodness
> — that is to say spiced chicken sausage, chunks of sweet potato, and tender
> curly kale. And because no good brothy bowl is complete without some bread
> for dunking, we're also throwing in buttery, herby toast points. Get ready for
> a meal as satisfying as it is delicious.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Place @butter{2%tbsp} and a @Italian Seasoning{pinch} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; bring to room temperature. Wash and dry all produce.

> TIP: If you have a toaster oven, feel free to skip preheating.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Peel and dice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%oz}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir sweet potato, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @Italian Seasoning{1%tsp}, @water{2 1/2%cups}, and a big pinch of @salt{} into pot. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium and simmer for ~{7%minutes}.

> Use the rest of the Italian Seasoning as you like.

Once soup has simmered for 7 minutes, uncover pot and stir in kale. Simmer, uncovered, until kale has wilted and sweet potato is tender, ~{5-7%minutes} more. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, mix @butter{2%tbsp}(softened) and @Italian Seasoning{1%tsp} in #small bowl{} until thoroughly combined. Season with @salt{}.

> TIP: If butter is not yet softened, microwave for 5-10 seconds.

Halve @demi-baguette{1}; spread herb butter onto cut sides. Toast cut sides up on top rack (or in a #toaster oven{}) until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Halve each baguette piece on a diagonal.

Divide soup between bowls and top with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Serve with toast points on the side.